  "text": "In this context, it is noteworthy that SHR is found in both the nucleus and cytoplasm of the stele, where it is produced. From there, SHR moves exactly one cell diameter, into the adjacent endodermis, where it is located entirely in the nucleus [CITATION_1] ). This observation is consistent with a model in which SHR gets trapped in the nuclei of the endodermis through interaction with a partner that causes translocation to the nucleus, similar to the AP3/PI interaction [CITATION_2] .",
